Paper: hep-th/0208098

Date: 2002-08-14

Title: Berry's phase in noncommutative spaces

Comments: 7 pages, no figure

We introduce the perturbative aspects of noncommutative quantum mechanics.Then we study the Berry's phase in the framework of noncommutative quantummechanics. The results show deviations from the usual quantum mechanics whichdepend on the parameter of space/space noncommtativity.